{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reform the education system to end standardised testing for 16-year-olds",
        "additional_details": "In many countries 16-year-olds are not required to take standardised tests. The Government should reform the education system and way schools are ranked with a view to bringing the standardised testing of 16-year-olds to an end.",
        "background": "GCSEs and other standardised tests are expensive, can cause unnecessary stress and anxiety for students, and can mean students end up simply being taught how to pass these tests.",
